          "type": "assistant",
          "text": "<proposed_plan>\n# Execution Plan: Topic Clustering\n\n## Summary\n\n- **Feature slug:** `20-topic-clustering`\n- **Artifact type:** `implementation-plan.md`\n- **Target doc path:** `docs/features/20-topic-clustering/implementation-plan.md`\n- Add a new **per-user topic clustering** feature built from existing processed-insight embeddings.\n- V1 is a **read-only discovery layer**: persisted background-generated topic groups with human-readable titles.\n- Each processed insight belongs to **zero or one** persisted topic group.\n- Topic groups stay **separate from tags and labels**, but each cluster exposes a read-only suggested label `{ category: \"Topic\", value: <cluster title> }`.\n- Clusters refresh **per affected user** after new processed insights arrive, with a nightly stale-user rebuild sweep.\n\n## Implementation Changes\n\n### Backend domain and storage\n\n- Add `InsightCluster`:\n  - `Id`, `OwnerUserId`, `Title`, `Description`, `KeywordsJson`, `MemberCount`, `RepresentativeProcessedInsightId`, `LastComputedAt`, `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt`\n- Add `InsightClusterMembership`:\n  - `InsightClusterId`, `ProcessedInsightId`, `Rank`, `SimilarityToCentroid`, `CreatedAt`\n  - unique constraint on `ProcessedInsightId` to enforce at most one cluster per insight\n- Keep clusters scoped strictly by `OwnerUserId`.\n- Do not backfill or mutate existing tags/labels.\n- Do not create a separate run-history table in v1; rely on Hangfire + logs/metrics for operational visibility.\n\n### Clustering algorithm and refresh behavior\n\n- Source set is **all `ProcessedInsight` rows with embeddings** for one owner.\n- Rebuild is **full per-owner replacement**, not incremental centroid mutation.\n- Rebuild steps:\n  1. Load all owner embeddings.\n  2. If the owner has fewer than `6` processed insights, delete existing clusters for that owner and stop.\n  3. Compute cosine similarity between owner insights.\n  4. For each insight, keep up to `5` nearest neighbors with similarity `>= 0.72`.\n  5. Create an undirected edge only for **mutual** nearest-neighbor pairs.\n  6. Convert connected components into candidate clusters.\n  7. Keep only components with size `>= 3`; smaller components remain unclustered.\n  8. Compute a centroid per kept cluster, rank members by similarity to centroid, and persist `Rank` plus `SimilarityToCentroid`.\n- Topic naming:\n  - Use the top `5` ranked member summaries as input to the existing chat-completions pipeline.\n  - Generate:\n    - `Title` max `60` chars\n    - `Description` max `160` chars\n    - `3` short keywords\n  - If title generation fails, fall back to a keyword-joined title from the top keywords.\n- Refresh triggers:\n  - enqueue `RebuildOwnerClustersAsync(ownerUserId)` with a short delay after a capture reaches `Completed`\n  - add a nightly recurring Hangfire job that rebuilds clusters only for owners whose `LastComputedAt` is older than `24` hours\n- Rebuild jobs must be idempotent and owner-scoped. Concurrent rebuilds for the same owner should no-op behind a per-owner lock.\n\n### Backend services and APIs\n\n- Add `IInsightClusteringService` for rebuild orchestration and cluster read models.\n- Add `ClustersController` with:\n  - `GET /api/v1/clusters`\n    - returns top topic groups for the current user ordered by `MemberCount desc`, then `UpdatedAt desc`\n  - `GET /api/v1/clusters/{id}`\n    - returns cluster metadata plus ordered member insights\n- Extend `GET /api/v1/dashboard/overview` to include `topicClusters`.\n- Extend capture detail read models so a processed insight can include an optional `cluster` summary with `id`, `title`, `description`, and `suggestedLabel`.\n- Public DTOs:\n  - `TopicClusterSummaryDto`\n    - `id`, `title`, `description`, `keywords`, `memberCount`, `updatedAt`, `representativeInsights`, `suggestedLabel`\n  - `TopicClusterDetailDto`\n    - summary fields plus `members`\n  - `TopicClusterMembershipDto`\n    - `processedInsightId`, `title`, `summary